# [IRTFOPEN](../wg/irtfopen.html)

## Summary
The IRTFOPEN session at IETF 125 featured two Applied Networking Research Prize (ANRP) award presentations and a strategic discussion on internetworking challenges for Artificial Intelligence (AI). The first ANRP talk by **Tianji Gao** focused on Secure Message Transport (SMT), a protocol designed to provide transport-level encryption for data centers while avoiding head-of-line blocking. The second ANRP talk by **Xiangjie Huang** presented ACE, a sending burstiness control mechanism for high-quality real-time communication (RTC). The final segment of the meeting, led by **Dirk Kutscher**, summarized previous discussions on AI workloads and solicited community feedback on potential research directions for the IRTF.

## Key Discussion Points

